RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) – Notes
1. What is RBAC

RBAC stands for Role-Based Access Control.

It is a security mechanism used to control who can access what resources and what actions they can perform in a system.

RBAC is commonly used in:

Kubernetes

AWS

Linux systems

Example:

Who can view pods

Who can create pods

Who can delete pods

2. Purpose of RBAC

The main purpose of RBAC is:

Improve system security

Prevent unauthorized access

Give limited permissions to users

Example:

User	Permission
Admin	Full access
Developer	Create and view pods
Viewer	Only view
3. RBAC Components in Kubernetes
1️⃣ Role

A Role defines what permissions are allowed.

Example: permission to read pods.

apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: Role
metadata:
  namespace: default
  name: pod-reader
rules:
- apiGroups: [""]
  resources: ["pods"]
  verbs: ["get", "watch", "list"]

This role allows a user to view pods.

2️⃣ RoleBinding

RoleBinding connects a Role to a user or group.

apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: RoleBinding
metadata:
  name: read-pods
  namespace: default
subjects:
- kind: User
  name: dev-user
roleRef:
  kind: Role
  name: pod-reader
  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
3️⃣ ClusterRole

A ClusterRole defines permissions for cluster-level resources.

Example:

nodes

storage

cluster resources

4️⃣ ClusterRoleBinding

ClusterRoleBinding assigns a ClusterRole to a user or group.

4. RBAC Flow
User → RoleBinding → Role → Permission

This means:

User gets a Role through RoleBinding

Role defines what actions the user can perform

5. Practical Example (EKS + IAM Role)

I created an EKS cluster in AWS.

Step 1

First, I created an EKS cluster.

Step 2

Then I attached an IAM Role to the cluster.

Step 3

After that, I connected the cluster from my server.

Command used:

aws eks update-kubeconfig --region us-east-1 --name Ajay

This command updated the kubeconfig file, allowing kubectl to communicate with the cluster.

Step 4

Then I created another new EKS cluster.

Step 5

I connected this cluster using the same IAM Role.

Step 6

After setting up the cluster, I ran the command:

kubectl get nodes

Result:

The nodes were displayed successfully.

This means:

The IAM Role allowed access

RBAC permissions allowed the user to interact with the cluster

6. Benefits of RBAC

Improves system security

Prevents unauthorized access

Provides limited access to users

Makes cluster management easier
